[3]
Date: Tue 14 Jun 2011
Source: YTN [in Korean, machine trans. edited]
http://www.ytn.co.kr/_ln/0103_201106142243170302


The 36-year-old mother who was treated for severe lung infection has
died. This is the 4th death in a family. After an induced birth,
symptoms deteriorated, and a single lung transplant was done. Acute
rejection occurred, and she died of hemorrhage and complications.

A family of suspected [lung disease] cases were reported during the
outbreak. A 26-year-old mother and her 23-month-old son were involved
late last month [May 2011]. Health authorities are conducting
investigations. However, the conclusion was not different from
patients with extensive lung damage from the disease. Severe
inflammation was found in the bronchioles, but the alveoli were in
relatively good condition. The deaths occurred sequentially.

