******
[4]
Date: Wed 15 Jun 2011
Source: KBS News [in Korean, machine trans. edited]
http://news.kbs.co.kr/society/2011/06/15/2307759.html


Last April [2011], a large hospital in Seoul treated a pregnant woman
for lung disease, and yesterday [14 Jun 2011] she died. This is the
most recent case of severe lung disease of unknown [etiology], and the
number of deaths has risen to 4.

"I do not know the cause or prevention of the disease," said the
[Korean] CDC Director. "A large-scale, long-term government funded
investigation [is needed? will be done?] to clearly identify the cause
of the disease. Similar disease has occurred in the past, but this is
the 1st time a systematic investigation is being done." A case
definition of the disease will made as soon as the data are collected
and analyzed. In an interview with a Ulsan University staff member, he
stated: "The possibility of infection is very low, but open, and I am
looking into it. In addition, environmental toxins are [may be?]
involved, or something like this, and I have planned to investigate
that."

Identification of unknown causes of diseases like this would take a
minimum of one year, health officials said.

